$ Oracle: DBTIMEZONE / SESSIONTIMEZONE

`dbtimezone` and `sessiontimezone` return the value of the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database[database's] or → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/session[session] timezone
either in `+hh:mm` format or as name of a → development/date-time/time-zone, depending on the most recent modification
of the time zone using `create database` or `alter database` or `alter session set time_zone`.

gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQL/functions/date_related/dbtimezone.sql||

gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQL/functions/date_related/sessiontimezone.sql||

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types/_timezone

  Other → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/functions/date[date related SQL functions]
